1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 1-01-34 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to gender usage in the North Dakota Century Code.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 1-01-34 of the North Dakota Century Code is amended
5 and reenacted as follows:
6 1-01-34. Gender - Definition.
7 Words of one gender include the other gendersused to reference an individual's sex,
8 gender, gender identity, or gender expression, mean the individual's determined sex at birth,
9 male or female.
10 1. Words referring to an individual, person, employer, employee, contestant, participant,
11 member, student, or juvenile must be used in the context of that person's sex as
12 determined at birth.
13 2. If sex, gender, gender identity, or gender expression is contested, determination is
14 established by the individual's DNA.
15 3. This section applies to all policies, records, forms, rules, standards, procedures,
16 guides, materials, instruction, training, correspondence, advertising, or marketing used
17 by any entity receiving state funding, including a public school, an institution under the
18 control of the state board of higher education, and a state agency or office.
